Since President, Vladimir Putin sent his troops into Ukraine, they have increasingly targeted civilians, killing and raping the women.
According to reports from The times, a woman claimed that Russian soldiers raped her with her child crying in the same house.
According to a tweet from Ukrainian Journalist, Anastasiia Lapatina, a Russian woman was heard in an intercepted call telling her partner to rape Ukrainian women, but should use protection while commiting the act.
Aanstasiia Lapatina tweeted: “I really thought I’ve seen the worst of it. But I just heard an intercepted call of a Russian woman telling her partner to rape Ukrainian women, just not tell about it.”
This tweet from Lapatina of woman heard telling her partner to rape Ukrainian women during the war has attracted reactions online, as some said she should be held accountable for their war crimes while some believe its Diabolical.
